The US amends the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves before their consultation with the consulate at the visa application services; costs will be reduced in this way.
As from 10 January 2011, the procedures for requesting a visa in the United States Embassy and in the consulates will be changed.
The new procedure requires most applicants to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their consultation in the Consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant that will be checked by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
Reduce the total cost of processing the visa, because it is no longer necessary to pay the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out separately.
The applicant makes only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who wish to extend their visa only do not need to have a conversation in the consulate, they just have to introduce themselves to the next ASC, where they present their documents and take their fingerprints.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second date for the conversation in the consulate remain less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Chihuahua, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service charge of 26 dollars.
Additional information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
